	title="in Clapham"
	highlight="Hydrotherapy"
	heroSubtitle="Physiotherapy delivered in water to facilitate movement and resistance exercises whilst reducing load on joints and tissues."
	breadcrumb="Hydrotherapy"
	seoTitle="Hydrotherapy in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Guided hydrotherapy in Clapham South. Water-based rehabilitation using buoyancy, resistance and warmth to help you move, rebuild strength and recover."
	intro={[
		"Hydrotherapy is a form of physiotherapy delivered in water, facilitating movement and resistance exercises whilst reducing load on joints and tissues.",
		"At Balance, hydrotherapy is used as part of a structured rehabilitation plan. The properties of water — buoyancy, resistance, and warmth — allow you to move more freely, build strength, and regain confidence where land-based exercise may be limited.",
		"Sessions are always guided by a physiotherapist and tailored to your specific condition and stage of recovery.",
	]}
	whenHeading="When to consider"
	whenHighlight="hydrotherapy"
	whenIntro="You may benefit if you experience:"
	whenList={[
		"Joint pain or stiffness limiting movement on land",
		"Post-surgical restrictions (e.g. knee, hip, or spinal surgery)",
		"Difficulty weight-bearing due to pain or weakness",
		"Reduced mobility following injury or illness",
		"Multiple areas of weakness and limitation",
		"Balance or coordination difficulties",
	]}
	howHeading="How we"
	howHighlight="work"
	howIntro="Sessions may include:"
	howList={[
		"Guided mobility and range of movement exercises",
		"Strength work using water resistance",
		"Balance and control exercises in a supported environment",
		"Gait re-education and functional movement practice",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Post-operative patients recovering from joint replacement or orthopaedic surgery",
		"Individuals with chronic pain requiring lower-load movement environments",
		"Seniors improving strength, balance, and confidence",
		"Neurological patients working on coordination and mobility",
		"Active individuals maintaining conditioning during injury recovery",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What should I bring?", a: "Swimming kit, towel, toiletries, and water for hydration." },
		{ q: "Do I need to be a swimmer?", a: "No. Most exercises are performed in a standing or supported position where your feet remain on the floor." },
		{ q: "How long does a session last?", a: "A typical session of hydrotherapy lasts 30 to 45 minutes, but you should set aside around 60 to 75 minutes in total." },
		{ q: "Can it help with back pain?", a: "Yes. The buoyancy of the water takes the pressure off the spinal discs and joints, while the warmth helps to decrease muscle guarding and spasms." },
		{ q: "Who is hydrotherapy unsuitable for?", a: "Those with open wounds, active skin infections, severe heart or lung conditions, or recent stomach issues." },
	]}
